SIMPLE: firing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Firing
<hw>Fir"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of discharging
firearms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The mode of introducing fuel into the furnace and
working it.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The application of fire, or of a cautery.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The process of partly vitrifying pottery by exposing
it to intense heat in a kiln.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Fuel; firewood or coal.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Firing iron</b></col>, <cd>an instrument used in
cauterizing.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 563 --></p>

<p><ent>Firing pin</ent>⟦br⟧
